.SH NAME
. \"
SAPHanaSR_with_DR_HA \- SAPHanaSR with HA cluster at DR site.
.PP
- DRAFT -
.PP
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\"
\fB*\fP Overview
.PP
.\" TODO
Two HANA system replication pairs are connected by HANA system replication.
The first site of the DR region is registered to the primary of the production
region, this replication is sync, syncmem or async.
The second site of the DR region is registered to the first site of the DR
region, this replication is sync or syncmem. 
The Linux clusters have no control over HANA system replication between the
production region and the DR region.
.br
[ A <= B' ] -> [ C => D ]
.\" TODO wording, naming convention
.PP
At the DR standby cluster, the SAPHanaController resource is configured for
DR mode.
.PP
.B The SAPHanaSR with HA cluster at DR site scenario is a technology preview.
.PP
\fB*\fP Setup procedure
.PP
TODO
.PP
.\"
.SH EXAMPLES
.\"
The examples are outlining highlevel procedures as well as describing basic tasks.
Detailled runbooks can be created by using the appropriate tasks for adding details
to the procedures.
.\" TODO disclaimer, particularly on takeover decision for async replication.
.PP
\fB*\fP Procedure for taking over to DR region in DR case./
.PP
.\" TODO
Cluster is up and running in DR mode on DR region nodes, HANA is up and running
in DR mode there as well.
SAPHanaController parameter "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=DR" is set.
All site names have to be same as already known to the cluster.
Example for scale-up.
Make sure to check for sane and idle status of Linux cluster and HANA before and
after each step.
Details on how to perform the steps can be found in additional examples below
and in manual page SAPHanaSR_maintenance_examples(7). See also SAP note 2517805.
SID is HA1, instance number is 00.
.PP
.RS 2
site1, node1: former production primary, currently down
.br
site2, node2: former production secondary, currently down
.br
site3, node3: current first DR replication target, to become production primary
.br
site4, node4: current second DR replication target, to become production secondary
.RE
.PP
Note: Understand the impact before trying.
.PP
.RS 2
1. Collect information and prepare parameter sheet.
.PP
2. Make sure both sites of the production region (site1, site2) are not running.
.PP
3. Take decision for takeover to third site (site3).
.PP
.B The next steps will invalidate all HANA data at former production sites.
.PP
4. Set SAPHanaController multi-state resource into maintenance. 
.RS 4
node3 # crm resource maintenance mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
5. Perform takeover at third site (site3).
.RS 4
node3 # su - ha1adm
.br
node3 ~> hdbnsutil -sr_takeover
.br
node3 ~> cdpy; python3 ./systemReplicationStatus.py; echo RC:$?
.RE
.PP
6. Change SAPHanaController "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=DR" to "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=yes".
.RS 4
node3 # crm configure set rsc_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00.PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER yes
.RE
.PP
7. Refresh SAPHanaController multi-state resource.
.RS 4
node3 # crm resource refresh mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
8. Get SAPHanaController multi-state resource out of maintenance.
.RS 4
node3 # crm resource maintenance mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00 off
.RE
.PP
9. Activate IPaddr2 resource at new production region.
.RS 4
.\" TODO check how to handle IP address
node3 # crm resource maintenance rsc_ip_HA1_HDB00 off
.br
node3 # crm resource start rsc_ip_HA1_HDB00 
.RE
.PP
10. Check that everything looks fine.
.RE
.PP
\fB*\fP Procedure for registering former production as new DR to new production region.
.PP
\" TODO
At all nodes the automatic start of cluster at boot has to be disabled.
All site names have to be same as already known to the cluster.
Example for scale-up.
Details on how to perform the steps can be found in additional examples below
and in manual page SAPHanaSR_maintenance_examples(7).
SID is HA1, instance number is 00.
.PP
.RS 2
site1, node1: currently idle, to become first DR replication target
.br
site2, node2: currently idle, to become second DR replication target
.br
site3, node3: production primary
.br
site4, node4: production secondary
.RE
.PP
Note: Understand the impact before trying.
.PP
.RS 2
1. Collect information and prepare parameter sheet.
.PP
2. Start Linux cluster on first DR node only (node1).
.RS 4
node1 # crm cluster start
.RE
.PP
3. Disable IPaddr2 resource.
.RS 4
node1 # crm resource stop rsc_ip_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
4. Set SAPHanaController multi-state resource into maintenance.
.RS 4
node1 # crm resource maintenance mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00
.br
node1 # crm resource maintenance rsc_ip_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
5. Change SAPHanaController "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=yes" to "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=DR".
.RS 4
node1 # crm configure set rsc_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00.PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER DR
.RE
.PP
6. Start Linux cluster on second DR node (node2).
.RS 4
node2 # crm cluster start
.RE
.PP
.B The next steps will overwrite all HANA data at site1 and site2.
.PP
7. Register first DR node (node1) as secondary to current primary (node3).
.RS 4
node1 # su - ha1adm
.br
node1 ~> hdbnsutil -sr_register --remoteHost=node3 --remoteInstance=00 \
.br
 --replicationMode=async --operationMode=logreplay \
.br
 --force_full_replica --name=site1
.RE
.PP
8. Enable system replication at first DR node (node1).
.RS 4
node1 # su - ha1adm
.br
node1 ~> hdbnsutil -sr_enable --name=site1
.RE
.PP
9. Register second DR node (node2) as secondary to first DR node (node1).
.RS 4
node1 # su - ha1adm
.br
node1 ~> hdbnsutil -sr_register --remoteHost=node1 --remoteInstance=00 \
.br
 --replicationMode=syncmem --operationMode=logreplay \
.br
 --force_full_replica --name=site2
.RE
.PP
10. Refresh SAPHanaController multi-state resource.
.RS 4
node1 # crm resource refresh mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
11. Get SAPHanaController multi-state resources out of maintenance.
.RS 4
node1 # crm resource maintenance mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00 off
.RE
.PP
12. Check that everything looks fine.
.RE
.PP
\fB*\fP Procedure for taking over to third site and registering first one while all sites keep running.
.PP
\" TODO
Third site is up and running with system replication enabled.
All site names have to be same as already known to the cluster.
Example for scale-up.
Details on how to perform the steps can be found in additional examples below
and in manual page SAPHanaSR_maintenance_examples(7).
SID is HA1, instance number is 00.
.PP
.RS 2
site1, node1: current production primary, to become first DR replication target
.br
site2, node2: current production primary secondary, to become second DR replication target
.br
site3, node3: current first DR replication target, to become production primary
.br
site4, node4: current second DR replication target, to become production secondary
.RE
.PP
Note: Understand the impact before trying.
.PP
.RS 2
1.1 Collect information and prepare parameter sheet.
.PP
.B The next steps will invalidate all HANA data at former production sites.
.PP
2.1 Disable IPaddr2 resource at first site (site1).
.RS 4
node1 # crm resource stop rsc_ip_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
2.2 Set SAPHanaController multi-state resource into maintenance at first site (site1).
.RS 4
node1 # crm resource maintenance SAPHanaController
.RE
.PP
2.3 Change SAPHanaController "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=yes" to "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=DR" at first site (site1).
.RS 4
node1 # crm configure set rsc_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00.PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER DR
.RE
.PP
3.1 Perform takeover at third site (site3).
.RS 4
node3 # su - ha1adm
.br
node3 ~> hdbnsutil -sr_takeover --suspendPrimary
.br
node3 ~> cdpy; python3 ./systemReplicationStatus.py; echo RC:$?
.RE
.PP
3.2 Set SAPHanaController multi-state resource into maintenance at third site (site3).
.RS 4
node3 # crm resource maintenance mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
3.3 Change SAPHanaController "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=DR" to "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=yes" at third site (site3).
.RS 4
node3 # crm configure set rsc_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00.PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER DR
.RE
.PP
3.4 Refresh SAPHanaController multi-state resource at third site (site3).
.RS 4
node3 # crm resource refresh mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
3.5 Get SAPHanaController multi-state out of maintenance third site (site3).
.RS 4
node3 # crm resource maintenance mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00 off
.RE
.PP
3.6 Activate IPaddr2 resource at third site (site3).
.RS 4
node3 # crm resource start rsc_ip_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
3.7 Check that everything looks fine so far.
.PP
.B The next steps will overwrite all HANA data at site1 and site2.
.PP
4.1 Register former production primary as secondary (site1) to new production primary (site3).
.RS 4
node1 # su - ha1adm
.br
node1 ~> hdbnsutil -sr_register --remoteHost=node3 --remoteInstance=00 \\
.br
 --replicationMode=async --operationMode=logreplay \\
.br
 --force_full_replica --name=site1
.RE
.PP
4.2 Refresh SAPHanaController multi-state resource at first site (site1).
.RS 4
node1 # crm resource refresh mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00
.RE
.PP
4.3 Get SAPHanaController multi-state out of maintenance at first site (site1).
.RS 4
node1 # crm resource maintenace mst_SAPHanaCon_HA1_HDB00 off
.RE
.PP
4.4 Check that everything looks fine.
.RE
.PP
\fB*\fP Entry in gobal.ini to register secondaries on takeover.
.PP
This entry is needed at all HANA nodes to allow ocf_suse_SAPHanaController(7)
parameter AUTOMATED_REGISTER=true in multi-target environments. The HANA has to
be stopped before the files can be edited. Do not copy the file between
nodes. Please check SAP HANA documentation for details.
.PP
.R2 2
[system_replication]
.br
 ...
.br
register_secondaries_on_takeover = true
 ...
.RE
.PP
\fB*\fP Copying HANA secure keystore from primary to secondaries at DR region.
.PP
Needs to be done at production primary before registering the DR secondaries.
DR secondary nodes are node3 and node4, SID is HA1.
.PP
.RS 2
# cd /usr/sap/HA1/SYS/global/security/rsecssfs
.br
# md5sum */*
.br
# rsync -va * node3:$PWD/
.br
# rsync -va * node4:$PWD/
.br
# ssh node3 "md5sum $PWD/*/*"
.br
# ssh node4 "md5sum $PWD/*/*"
.RE
.PP
\fB*\fP Registering first DR node as secondary to production primary.
.PP
Needs to be done at first DR node.
DR site is site3, production primary is node1, SID is HA1, instance numner is 00.
.PP
.RS 2
# su - ha1adm
.br
~> HDB info
.br
~> hdbnsutil -sr_register --remoteHost=node1 --remoteInstance=00 \\
.br
 --replicationMode=async --operationMode=logreplay --name=site3 \\
.br
 --online
.br
~> hdbnsutil -sr_state
.br
.RE
.PP
\fB*\fP Backing up first DR node and enabling system replication.
.PP
Needs to be done at first DR node, before registering another node.
First DR site is site3, SID is HA1, instance number is 00.
.PP
.RS 2
# su - ha1adm
.br
~> hdbsql -i 00 -u SYSTEM -d SYSTEMDB \\
.br
 "BACKUP DATA FOR FULL SYSTEM USING FILE ('backup')"
.br
~> hdbnsutil -sr_enable --name=site3
.br
~> hdbnsutil -sr_state
.RE
.PP
\fB*\fP Registering second DR node to first one.
.PP
Nees to be done at second DR node.
SID is HA1, site is site4, first DR node is node3, instance number is 00.
Needs first DR node up and running.
.PP
.RS 2
# su - ha1adm
.br
~> HDB info
.br
~> hdbnsutil -sr_register --remoteHost=node3 --remoteInstance=00 \\
.br
 --replicationMode=syncmem --operationMode=logreplay --name=site4 \\
.br
 --online
.br
~> hdbnsutil -sr_state
.RE
.PP
.\"
.SH FILES
.\"
.TP
/hana/shared/$SID/global/hdb/custom/config/global.ini
on-disk representation of HANA global system configuration.
.TP
/usr/sap/$SID/SYS/global/security/rsecssfs/
HANA database secure keystore directory.
.PP
.\"
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.\"
.\" TODO \fB*\fP SAPHanaSR-angi version 1.3.??? or later.
.PP
\fB*\fP Only one system replication between the two SAP HANA databases in the Linux
cluster. Maximum one system replication to an HANA database outside the Linux cluster.
.PP 
\fB*\fP The replication mode is either sync or syncmem for the controlled replication.
Replication mode async is not supported inside the Linux cluster.
.PP
\fB*\fP Once an HANA system replication site is known to the Linux cluster, that
exact site name has to be used whenever the site is registered manually. At any
time only one site is configured as primary replication source.
.PP
\fB*\fP No Multi-SID scenario.
.PP
\fB*\fP "register_secondaries_on_takeover = true" is needed at all HANA sites at
production region and DR region.
.PP
\fB*\fP All HANA sites need to have the same content in their HANA secure keystore.
.PP
\fB*\fP Sufficient disk space for transaction logs and log backup at each potential
replication source. Housekeeping might also help.
.PP
\fB*\fP The Linux clusters have no control over HANA system replication between the
production region and the DR region.
.PP
\fB*\fP Before connecting the DR region to the production region, the production
SAPHanaSR-angi scale-up performance-optimized cluster needs to be up and running.
.PP
\fB*\fP Before connecting the DR region to the production region, the DR region
has been set up as SAPHanaSR-angi scale-up performance-optimized cluster and the
whole cluster has been set into maintenance.
.PP
\fB*\fP The first site of the DR region is registered to the primary of the
production region, this replication is sync, syncmem or async.
The second site of the DR region is registered to the first site of the DR region,
this replication is sync or syncmem. 
.br
[ A <= B' ] -> / C => D /
.PP
\fB*\fP The SAPHanaController parameter "PREFER_SITE_TAKEOVER=DR" has to be set
at the DR standby cluster. In case of manual DR takeover, this parameter needs to
be changed. See manual page ocf_suse_SAPHanaController(7).
.PP
.\" TODO \fB*\fP Production HA cluster and DR HA cluster must never be active at the same time.
.PP
\fB*\fP At all nodes the automatic start of cluster at boot has to be disabled.
.PP
\fB*\fP The HA cluster moves an IP address with the HANA primary between the two
production nodes. The IP address will not be moved from production region to DR
region. 
.PP
\fB*\fP Decision and procedure for takeover to DR region are in customer´s
responsibility. All need to comply to SAP HANA requirements, please refer to SAP
documentation for details.
.PP
\fB*\fP Any manual procedure has to be tested, documented and trained before applied
on production systems.
.PP
See also the REQUIREMENTS section in manual pages SAPHanaSR(7) and susHanaSR.py(7). 
